                            <entry>+10</entry><entry>+9</entry><entry>+4</entry><entry>+10 (mixed)</entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>IV</entry><entry>8 (Large)</entry><entry>2</entry><entry>12</entry>
                            <entry>+15</entry><entry>+12</entry><entry>+6</entry><entry>+15</entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>V</entry><entry>10 (Large)</entry><entry>2</entry><entry>16</entry>
                            <entry>+20</entry><entry>+15</entry><entry>+8</entry><entry>+21</entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>VI</entry><entry>12 (Huge)</entry><entry>3</entry><entry>20</entry>
                            <entry>+30</entry><entry>+18</entry><entry>+10</entry><entry>+28</entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>VII</entry><entry>15 (Huge)</entry><entry>3</entry><entry>24</entry>
                            <entry>+40</entry><entry>+21</entry><entry>+10</entry><entry>+36</entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>VIII</entry><entry>18 (Enormous)</entry><entry>4</entry><entry>28</entry>
                            <entry>+50</entry><entry>+24</entry><entry>+12</entry><entry>+45</entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </table>

                <para>
                    Fire elementals are immune to most physical attacks,
                    save for those that smother them, or water based
                    attacks. Air attacks can also put them out, though
                    their soak is doubled versus such. Throwing water
                    at it will generally do +1 damage per litre of water
                    each round.
                </para>

                <para>
                    All the time there is more combustable material, the
                    elemental will regenerate one body level per size
                    category above tiny each round.
                </para>

                <para>
                    Fire elemental shed a <e>lot</e> of heat. Anyone close
                    to it automatically takes damage equal to half its
                    normal attack damage each round. <e>Close</e> is
                    within 1m for a small elemental, 2m for medium, 3m
                    for large etc. If the damage is greater than +5,
                    half that damage is applied out to another multiple
                    of distance, and so on.
                </para>
                
                <para>
                    The core temperate of a fire elemental is approximately
                    150C, +50C per rank.
                </para>
            </physical>

            <tactics>
                <para>
                    A fire elemental has a brawl skill equal to its
                    rank + 2. It cannot be parried except with a shield
                    or a shield like weapon.
                </para>
            </tactics>
